---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Spices — Flavourful Terms That Score Big"
  description="Spice words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. SAFFRON (13pts), PAPRIKA (15pts), CAYENNE (12pts). Season your game with high-scoring spice vocabulary."
  keywords="scrabble spice words, saffron scrabble points, paprika scrabble, cayenne scrabble, spice vocabulary scrabble, cooking words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Spices — Flavourful Terms That Score Big","description":"Spice words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. SAFFRON (13pts), PAPRIKA (15pts), CAYENNE (12pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-spices"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PAPRIKA a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PAPRIKA scores 15 points (P=3, A=1, P=3, R=1, I=1, K=5, A=1). The K=5 tile drives the score. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play SAFFRON in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. SAFFRON scores 13 points (S=1, A=1, F=4, F=4, R=1, O=1, N=1) as a 7-letter bingo candidate. Using both F tiles (worth 4 each) makes this a high-value play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is CAYENNE valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! CAYENNE scores 12 points (C=3, A=1, Y=4, E=1, N=1, N=1, E=1). The Y=4 and C=3 combination gives it solid scoring from a 7-letter word."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Spices — Flavourful Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Your spice rack is hiding some serious Scrabble firepower. Spice names are packed with F tiles, K tiles, and double letters that translate into impressive scores — especially since many land at exactly 7 letters for bingo potential.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PAPRIKA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SAFFRON</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CAYENNE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TURMERIC</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Spice Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">PAPRIKA — 15 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">P=3, A=1, P=3, R=1, I=1, K=5, A=1 · 7 letters · Bingo candidate</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A red spice made from dried peppers. PAPRIKA uses double P=3 and K=5 for a 15-point base. As a 7-letter word, it delivers 65 total with the bingo bonus — a spicy play indeed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌿 SAFFRON</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · S=1, A=1, F=4, F=4, R=1, O=1, N=1 · Double F bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌶️ CAYENNE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · C=3, A=1, Y=4, E=1, N=1, N=1, E=1 · 7-letter bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧡 TURMERIC</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · T=1, U=1, R=1, M=3, E=1, R=1, I=1, C=3 · 8 letters</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫚 GINGER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · G=2, I=1, N=1, G=2, E=1, R=1 · Common tiles</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Everyday Spice Words</h2>
      <p>Common kitchen spices provide reliable mid-range plays that work from frequently drawn tiles:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CLOVE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CUMIN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FENNEL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CINNAMON</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PEPPER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NUTMEG</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Spice Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Three 7-letter bingos in one category:</span> PAPRIKA (15+50=65), SAFFRON (13+50=63), and CAYENNE (12+50=62) are all bingo-length. Keep these letter patterns in mind when you hold F, K, or Y tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SAFFRON uses both F tiles:</span> With F=4 each, SAFFRON extracts maximum value from the bag's two F tiles. If you draw both early, this should be top of mind.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PEPPER has hook potential:</span> PEPPERS adds S, PEPPERED adds ED. The double P=3 base of 12 points grows further with common suffixes.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Spice words are <span class="text-white font-medium">F-tile and K-tile specialists</span>. SAFFRON uses both F=4 tiles, PAPRIKA uses K=5, and CAYENNE leverages Y=4. This category solves the common problem of difficult consonant-heavy racks.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-cooking/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Cooking</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-food-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Food Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-baking/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Baking</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid spice word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
